♪ Oh, mother, dear, we're
not the fortunate ones ♪

06:24.675 --> 06:27.234
♪ And girls, they wanna have fun ♪

06:27.234 --> 06:32.234
♪ Oh, girls just wanna have fun ♪

06:35.467 --> 06:37.589
♪ The phone rings in the
middle of the night ♪

06:37.589 --> 06:41.174
♪ My father yells what you
gonna do with your life ♪

06:41.174 --> 06:43.743
♪ Oh, daddy, dear, you know
you're still number one ♪

06:43.743 --> 06:46.379
♪ And girls, they wanna have fun ♪

06:46.379 --> 06:48.467
♪ Oh, girls, just wanna have ♪

06:48.467 --> 06:51.531
♪ That's all they really want ♪

06:51.531 --> 06:54.165
♪ Some fun ♪

06:54.165 --> 06:56.540
♪ When the working day is done ♪

06:56.540 --> 06:58.180
Which one are you?

06:58.180 --> 06:59.570
- I'm not in this one.

06:59.570 --> 07:02.253
They're doing lyrical. I do jazz and tap.

07:03.090 --> 07:03.923
- Nice.

07:05.520 --> 07:07.540
- My best friend Carly's
in this one though.

07:07.540 --> 07:10.493
She's right there.

07:10.493 --> 07:14.090
(upbeat pop music)

07:14.090 --> 07:14.923
- Nice.

07:19.250 --> 07:20.783
- Isn't she just so pretty.

07:22.362 --> 07:23.307
- [Mr. Problem] I don't
think there's a problem.

07:23.307 --> 07:26.166
Worked just fine all the way over here.

07:26.166 --> 07:28.132
- Oh.
- Shift's perfect now.

07:28.132 --> 07:29.549
Just so you know.

07:31.077 --> 07:33.599
Hey, is that the you over there, Bridget?

07:33.599 --> 07:34.659
- [Bridget] Yes.

07:34.659 --> 07:36.120
- [Grandma] Bridget, tell Mr. Dodge

07:36.120 --> 07:37.370
what you told me last night.

07:37.370 --> 07:39.520
- I don't know what I told you.

07:39.520 --> 07:41.670
- [Grandma] Oh, well
she said she wants to be

07:41.670 --> 07:42.503
a teacher too.

07:44.360 --> 07:45.754
- Is that right, Bridget.

07:45.754 --> 07:48.234
♪ Girls ♪

07:48.234 --> 07:50.887
♪ They just wanna, they just wanna ♪

07:50.887 --> 07:53.554
(ominous music)

08:15.890 --> 08:17.240
- So you're a teacher, huh?

08:18.420 --> 08:19.253
- That's right.

08:22.170 --> 08:23.310
I'm actually gonna be

08:23.310 --> 08:25.577
Bridget's English teacher next year.

08:25.577 --> 08:28.244
(ominous music)

08:30.600 --> 08:34.173
So are you going to pick up Carly?

08:36.090 --> 08:39.607
Carly Isle with the brown
hair and the freckles?

09:01.588 --> 09:05.546
- Did you know that he
married his student?

09:05.546 --> 09:06.470
- What?

09:06.470 --> 09:08.350
- It was a girl who was his student

09:08.350 --> 09:11.360
and then he married her
when she was a little older.

09:11.360 --> 09:13.170
But still, he knew her when she was young

09:13.170 --> 09:15.393
and then he married her.

09:17.070 --> 09:18.122
He's a creep.

09:18.122 --> 09:20.789
(ominous music)

09:48.310 --> 09:49.360
- You're Eddy, right?

09:50.338 --> 09:51.588
- [Eddy] Yeah.

09:52.460 --> 09:53.877
- I feel like I know everything about you.

09:53.877 --> 09:54.913
- Carly.
- Don't you live

09:54.913 --> 09:56.193
with your fiance?

09:57.090 --> 09:57.923
- I used to.

09:58.920 --> 10:00.020
- [Carly] Not anymore?

10:01.250 --> 10:02.640
- No.

10:02.640 --> 10:04.570
- Why?
- He just doesn't.

10:04.570 --> 10:06.270
He just moved here for the summer.

10:07.410 --> 10:09.660
- She basically had a
relationship with her boss

10:09.660 --> 10:10.900
who's 20 years older than her

10:10.900 --> 10:12.623
and married and has two kids.

10:15.140 --> 10:17.420
I went to his house at night
and smashed some windows

10:17.420 --> 10:18.570
and messed up his lawn.

10:29.938 --> 10:32.855
(traffic whirring)

10:34.304 --> 10:37.540
- Did you have a girlfriend
when you were our age?

10:37.540 --> 10:40.730
I'm just wondering because I
haven't had a boyfriend yet

10:40.730 --> 10:42.030
and neither has Bridgette.

10:43.350 --> 10:44.703
- [Eddy] I don't think that's a problem.

10:45.770 --> 10:47.310
- [Carly] But did you?

10:47.310 --> 10:48.410
When you were our age?

10:49.280 --> 10:51.083
- Yeah, I think so.

10:55.430 --> 10:56.263
- What happened?

10:58.843 --> 11:00.090
- I don't know. I don't really remember.

11:00.090 --> 11:01.240
It was a long time ago.

11:05.050 --> 11:06.350
- Do you want a boyfriend?

11:07.293 --> 11:08.600
- No, it sounds boring.

11:08.600 --> 11:10.260
- Yeah.

11:10.260 --> 11:11.610
And Annalise Billings got a boyfriend

11:11.610 --> 11:13.210
and now she's pregnant.

11:13.210 --> 11:14.163
And she's only 15.

11:18.370 --> 11:21.680
(boat motor buzzing)

11:21.680 --> 11:23.780
- [Carly] Someone one
time jumped from there,

11:23.780 --> 11:25.220
but she didn't know a boat was coming,

11:25.220 --> 11:26.550
so instead of landing in the water,

11:26.550 --> 11:27.890
she landed on the back of the boat.

11:27.890 --> 11:29.080
- It was really sad, actually.

11:29.080 --> 11:30.790
She broke both her legs and her arm.

11:30.790 --> 11:31.940
And now she's in a wheelchair

11:31.940 --> 11:33.350
- [Carly] I think she
landed on a guy in the boat,

11:33.350 --> 11:34.400
and he broke his arm.

11:36.390 --> 11:37.493
- Oh my God.

11:38.690 --> 11:39.853
Did you guys know her?

11:40.760 --> 11:42.270
- [Bridget] No.

11:42.270 --> 11:45.170
- Did you know Mr. Dodge is
gonna take me out on his boat?

11:47.520 --> 11:49.663
He does it with a group
of kids every summer.

11:51.350 --> 11:53.223
- Why didn't you tell me that before?

11:54.600 --> 11:55.433
- Forgot.

12:00.913 --> 12:03.913
(soft guitar music)

12:08.278 --> 12:09.994
(water spraying)
- Whoo!

12:09.994 --> 12:10.827
Come on!

12:13.924 --> 12:15.820
(Carly and Bridget laughing)

12:15.820 --> 12:18.820
(soft guitar music)

12:55.819 --> 12:56.652
Um...

12:58.820 --> 12:59.803
There you go.
- Oh, yeah.

12:59.803 --> 13:01.564
I like this.

13:01.564 --> 13:03.397
- We'll keep that. Oh.

13:04.690 --> 13:06.447
Variations of the-
- Whoa.

13:07.805 --> 13:09.017
Wizard robes!

13:09.017 --> 13:12.184
(gentle guitar music)

13:31.258 --> 13:33.737
(ominous music)

13:33.737 --> 13:34.654
- Do you...

13:36.650 --> 13:38.840
Do you have Arthur's phone number?

13:38.840 --> 13:40.190
- No.

13:40.190 --> 13:41.730
- He said he was getting phone calls

13:41.730 --> 13:43.300
in the middle of the night

13:43.300 --> 13:45.350
while we were at the conference together.

13:46.489 --> 13:49.406
- I don't know anything about that.

13:52.974 --> 13:57.974
(boat motors buzzing)
(birds chirping)

14:18.750 --> 14:21.300
Did you know Mr. Dodge
married one of his students?

14:22.953 --> 14:25.573
- (sighs) Well, she was older then.

14:27.370 --> 14:30.120
- Yeah, but it's still
kind of weird, isn't it?

14:30.120 --> 14:31.920
- Well they're not together anymore.

14:39.555 --> 14:42.472
(dishes clinking)

15:03.667 --> 15:06.681
- Are you gonna sleep here?

15:06.681 --> 15:08.264
- No, probably not.

15:18.919 --> 15:21.586
(ominous music)

15:29.933 --> 15:32.850
(text alert dings)

15:53.569 --> 15:56.569
(crickets chirping)

16:40.453 --> 16:43.120
(drill buzzing)

16:53.160 --> 16:53.993
Bridget?

16:57.280 --> 16:58.113
Grandma?

17:04.574 --> 17:07.324
(drill whirring)

17:10.377 --> 17:11.530
- Hey, Ed.

17:11.530 --> 17:12.363
- Hey.

17:14.118 --> 17:15.510
- Morning.

17:15.510 --> 17:16.343
- Good morning.

17:18.750 --> 17:19.583
What's going on?

17:21.280 --> 17:22.271
- Fixing the deck.

17:25.490 --> 17:26.740
What's going on with you?

17:32.210 --> 17:33.550
- Oh, well, ah...

17:34.541 --> 17:36.940
I'm not feeling great. Pretty tired.

17:36.940 --> 17:38.010
- Uh-huh.
- I think I'm gonna go

17:38.010 --> 17:40.018
lie down, actually.

17:40.018 --> 17:43.351
(door opens and closes)

17:56.505 --> 17:59.172
(ominous music)

18:03.005 --> 18:05.422
(phone taps)

18:08.719 --> 18:11.552
(heavy breathing)

18:30.373 --> 18:33.040
(intense music)

18:43.692 --> 18:46.359
(water running)

19:01.206 --> 19:04.039
(plane whirring)

19:23.000 --> 19:24.670
- That's where we're
gonna work next summer.

19:24.670 --> 19:25.979
- Yeah.

19:25.979 --> 19:27.430
- You know that already?

19:27.430 --> 19:28.530
- I'm gonna work in checkout

19:28.530 --> 19:30.300
and Bridget's gonna work
at the meat counter.

19:30.300 --> 19:32.600
- No, I am not working the meat counter.

19:32.600 --> 19:33.823
- That's what they said.

19:37.530 --> 19:40.420
- [Eddy] Hey, the meat
counter doesn't sound so bad.

19:40.420 --> 19:42.020
You get to learn about

19:42.020 --> 19:44.650
all the different cuts of meat

19:45.870 --> 19:47.913
and butchering and stuff.

19:50.643 --> 19:52.510
- This is Seth , Debbie and Gayle,

19:52.510 --> 19:54.360
and all the big boys.

19:54.360 --> 19:56.193
And this was the old ballroom.

19:57.030 --> 19:58.790
- [Bridget] Where was it?

19:58.790 --> 19:59.623
- To the left.

20:00.623 --> 20:03.490
- Like right here?
- No, further to the left.

20:03.490 --> 20:04.833
- There.
- No, there.

20:04.833 --> 20:08.110
- [Weatherman On TV] Colder
than yesterday at this time.

20:08.110 --> 20:09.150
- [Bridget] Who's that?

20:09.150 --> 20:10.380
- That's Millie Turnbow.

20:10.380 --> 20:11.470
- [Weatherman] There's
a temperature trend.

20:11.470 --> 20:12.540
We'll have a...
- It's a funny story

20:12.540 --> 20:13.373
about Millie.

20:14.300 --> 20:16.590
In the winter time, they
would drive their cars

20:16.590 --> 20:18.883
out onto the ice and
they'd go ice fishing.

20:19.720 --> 20:21.800
So one night the whole town was there

20:21.800 --> 20:23.750
and he had this big party

20:23.750 --> 20:25.579
and Millie stayed in the car.

20:25.579 --> 20:26.670
- [Weatherman] So a 30 degree day...

20:26.670 --> 20:28.683
- The ice melted and the car fell in.

20:29.990 --> 20:31.520
- And no one
- Jesus.

20:31.520 --> 20:34.170
- could go and help her
because it was just too cold.

20:35.240 --> 20:37.640
So in the summer they
brought the coast guard

20:37.640 --> 20:39.200
and some scuba divers,

20:39.200 --> 20:40.910
but they never found her body.

20:40.910 --> 20:43.900
- [Weatherman] I do think we'll
warm up to about 44 to 45.

20:43.900 --> 20:45.013
A mix of sun and clouds.

20:45.013 --> 20:46.028
- [Bridget] How old was she?

20:46.028 --> 20:47.910
- Oh, she couldn't have been
much older than you two.

20:47.910 --> 20:49.220
Maybe 16?

20:49.220 --> 20:50.720
She was engaged to be married.

20:55.625 --> 20:58.292
(ominous music)

21:12.160 --> 21:14.167
- It's looking pretty
good if you wanna get in.

21:22.260 --> 21:23.093
Bridget?

21:28.000 --> 21:29.250
- I'm not swimming today.

21:32.350 --> 21:33.510
- No, really. It's pretty clear.

21:33.510 --> 21:34.810
I can see a few feet down.

21:41.470 --> 21:43.751
- What if I touch the bones?

21:43.751 --> 21:45.418
- [Eddy] What bones?

21:48.760 --> 21:51.530
- The bones of the girl who drowned.

21:51.530 --> 21:53.813
Millie Turnbow, who feel through the ice.

21:53.813 --> 21:55.363
(ominous music)

21:55.363 --> 21:58.530
(boat motor buzzing)

22:23.430 --> 22:25.310
Can we go out for a walk?

22:25.310 --> 22:26.143
- What?

22:27.298 --> 22:32.298
- Can we go for a walk?

22:32.735 --> 22:35.402
(ominous music)

22:43.832 --> 22:45.630
Can we go for a drive?

22:45.630 --> 22:46.913
- Where would we drive?

22:49.466 --> 22:51.901
- We could just drive around.

22:51.901 --> 22:54.568
(ominous music)

23:57.579 --> 23:58.486
Okay, stop.

23:58.486 --> 24:01.153
(ominous music)

24:08.370 --> 24:10.237
This is where Mr. Dodge lives.

24:12.671 --> 24:14.921
- He lives here by himself?

24:24.614 --> 24:26.186
(suspenseful music)

24:26.186 --> 24:27.402
What's that sound?

24:27.402 --> 24:29.312
(distant bellowing)

24:29.312 --> 24:30.729
- [Bridget] What?

24:40.896 --> 24:43.896
(soft guitar music)

25:19.523 --> 25:22.273
(birds chirping)

26:33.444 --> 26:36.777
(indistinct chattering)

26:37.936 --> 26:39.590
(Bridget and Carly laughing)

26:39.590 --> 26:40.660
- Oh my God! I'm sorry.

26:40.660 --> 26:43.260
I didn't know. I should
have, I should have knocked.

26:44.510 --> 26:45.850
- It's okay. You can come in.

26:45.850 --> 26:47.163
- [Bridget] Yeah, come in.

26:51.350 --> 26:52.183
- What's going on?

26:52.183 --> 26:54.010
- [Carly] Eddy, what do
you think of my shirt?

26:54.010 --> 26:55.130
Is it too loose?

26:55.130 --> 26:56.460
- Yeah, I don't like it.
- It's like a boy's shirt.

26:56.460 --> 26:58.233
- [Eddy] No, I think it looks good.

26:59.360 --> 27:00.860
- Why don't you try it on?

27:00.860 --> 27:02.510
- I bet it'll look better on you.

27:16.700 --> 27:19.330
- Um, where's Grandma?

27:19.330 --> 27:20.680
- She's at the beauty shop.

27:23.098 --> 27:24.515
Oh my God.

27:24.515 --> 27:26.854
That was so embarrassing.
(Carly laughing)

27:26.854 --> 27:28.647
Please don't ever do that again.

27:28.647 --> 27:30.190
- [Carly] (laughing) I'm sorry.

27:30.190 --> 27:32.460
(phone ringing)

27:32.460 --> 27:33.877
- [Bridget] Okay.

27:34.747 --> 27:36.158
- [Carly] I can't believe
he actually started

27:36.158 --> 27:37.752
undoing his shirt!

27:37.752 --> 27:39.486
- [Bridget] He seemed drunk.

27:39.486 --> 27:40.987
(phone continues ringing)

27:40.987 --> 27:42.787
- She doesn't keep her phone on her?

28:03.632 --> 28:05.030
- [Grandma] Hi, Eddy.

28:05.030 --> 28:06.680
- You forgot your phone.

28:06.680 --> 28:08.720
- Ah, yep. You're right, I did.

28:08.720 --> 28:10.570
- I brought it for you.

28:10.570 --> 28:12.670
- [Mr. Dodge] What's up, Eddy?

28:12.670 --> 28:13.587
- [Grandma] Do you wanna get in?

28:13.587 --> 28:14.753
- No, I'm gonna walk.

28:16.480 --> 28:18.880
- Hey Eddy, you got any
plans for later tonight?

28:20.208 --> 28:21.100
(Eddy sighs)

28:21.100 --> 28:23.120
I thought maybe we could
get a beer or something.

28:23.120 --> 28:25.953
(birds chirping)

28:27.180 --> 28:28.830
- Yeah, I'm not feeling too good.

28:30.450 --> 28:31.400
I'll see.

28:31.400 --> 28:33.260
- Well, let me know. All right?

28:33.260 --> 28:34.890
- Yeah, we'll see.

28:34.890 --> 28:36.313
- All right. I'll see you later.

28:40.820 --> 28:42.910
- Okay. Okay.

28:42.910 --> 28:44.490
Okay. Okay.

28:44.490 --> 28:46.163
I'll talk to you later. Bye.

28:49.822 --> 28:50.905
- Who's that?

28:52.280 --> 28:55.490
- Oh, um, Arthur.

28:55.490 --> 28:56.323
My boss.

29:02.750 --> 29:04.230
- I didn't know your
smell came from lotion.

29:04.230 --> 29:06.103
I thought it was perfume or something.

29:15.397 --> 29:18.564
(footsteps pattering)

29:20.445 --> 29:23.876
(Bridget and Carly laughing)

29:23.876 --> 29:25.133
- [Bridget] We have to
finish this before we leave.

29:25.133 --> 29:26.466
- [Carly] Okay.

29:29.250 --> 29:31.343
- [Bridget] Chug, chug, chug, chug!

29:32.352 --> 29:33.185
(Carly coughing)

29:33.185 --> 29:35.730
(Bridget chuckles)

29:35.730 --> 29:36.940
Carly, no way.

29:36.940 --> 29:38.100
Oh my God! No!

29:39.731 --> 29:40.935
(plastic crinkling)

29:40.935 --> 29:42.425
(Carly coughing)

29:42.425 --> 29:47.425
- Oh my God.

29:47.763 --> 29:49.836
- Bye, Grandma. Bye, Eddie.

29:49.836 --> 29:50.669
- Bye.

29:59.894 --> 30:02.394
(door closes)

30:04.697 --> 30:07.364
(phone buzzing)

30:11.641 --> 30:14.308
(ominous music)

30:32.210 --> 30:35.711
(indistinct chattering)

30:35.711 --> 30:38.711
(soft guitar music)

30:51.638 --> 30:52.721
- Who's that?

30:55.889 --> 30:59.782
(ball clacks)
- That's Mark.

30:59.782 --> 31:01.032
- You know him?

31:02.941 --> 31:04.477
- Yep.

31:04.477 --> 31:05.483
- And the bartender?

31:09.600 --> 31:10.433
- Lisa.

31:23.509 --> 31:24.587
- Hi, Lisa.

31:24.587 --> 31:27.305
Get a couple of Coors Lights, please?

31:27.305 --> 31:30.722
(atmospheric rock music)

31:43.128 --> 31:45.593
Well, long time no see, son. How you been?

31:46.920 --> 31:48.370
- Hey, Bob.

31:48.370 --> 31:49.520
- [Bob] Who's this guy?

31:51.910 --> 31:55.293
- This is Eddie. He's
visiting from Chicago.

31:58.240 --> 31:59.720
- [Bob] Chi-Town, huh?

31:59.720 --> 32:01.160
- Wow, the nitty-gritty city.
- Whereabouts?

32:01.160 --> 32:02.660
Anywhere near Michigan Avenue?

32:05.470 --> 32:06.660
Christmas time we take the kids

32:06.660 --> 32:07.493
down to Michigan Avenue, look at the...

32:07.493 --> 32:09.440
The girls love it, all that action.

32:09.440 --> 32:10.393
The windows.

32:10.393 --> 32:11.565
(liquor trickling)

32:11.565 --> 32:13.397
(ominous music)

32:13.397 --> 32:16.730
(indistinct chattering)

32:18.439 --> 32:21.439
(liquor trickling)

32:38.840 --> 32:39.970
- Do you think that

32:41.120 --> 32:42.470
you've been the same person

32:43.950 --> 32:45.193
your entire life?

32:47.120 --> 32:50.780
- You know that thought
experiment that's like,

32:50.780 --> 32:52.030
if you have an ax

32:54.150 --> 32:56.170
and you replace the head of ax

32:56.170 --> 32:58.280
and then you replace the handle of the ax,

32:58.280 --> 32:59.803
is it the same ax?

33:01.460 --> 33:03.133
- What about Mr. Dodge?
- What?

33:04.796 --> 33:06.133
- What?

33:06.133 --> 33:07.889
- What did you just say?

33:07.889 --> 33:10.556
(ominous music)

33:28.092 --> 33:31.424
